james baker  wikipedia james baker from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search this article is about the politician for other uses see james baker disambiguation and james addison baker disambiguation james baker th and th white house chief of staff in office august   – january   president george h w bush preceded by samuel skinner succeeded by mack mclarty in office january   – february   president ronald reagan preceded by jack watson succeeded by don regan st united states secretary of state in office january   – august   president george h w bush preceded by george shultz succeeded by lawrence eagleburger th united states secretary of the treasury in office february   – august   president ronald reagan preceded by don regan succeeded by nicholas brady personal details born james addison baker iii  april   age  houston texas us political party democratic before  republican –present spouses mary stuart mchenry – susan garrett –present education princeton university university of texas signature military service allegiance  united states servicebranch  united states marine corps years of service – rank captain james addison jim baker iii born april   is an american attorney and statesman he served as white house chief of staff and united states secretary of the treasury under president ronald reagan and as us secretary of state and white house chief of staff under president george h w bush as secretary of state he helped oversee us foreign policy during the end of the cold war and dissolution of the soviet union as well as during the gulf war he is the namesake of the james a baker iii institute for public policy at rice university contents  early life and education  early political career  reagan administration  bush administration  postcabinet career  –  iraq  other advisory positions  world justice project  climate leadership council  personal life  honors  notes  further reading  works by  works about  external links early life and educationedit james addison baker was born in houston at  bissonnet the son of james a baker jr – and ethel bonner née means baker august   – april   his father was a partner of houston law firm baker botts baker has a sister bonner baker moffitt his grandfather was attorney and banker james a baker sr and his greatgrandfather was jurist and politician james addison baker the elder baker attended the hill school a boarding school in pottstown pennsylvania he graduated from princeton university in  with an ab in history cum laude he was a member of phi delta theta baker served in the united states marine corps  attaining the rank of first lieutenant and later rising to captain in the united states marine corps reserve afterwards he earned a jd  from the university of texas at austin and began to practice law in texas from  to  and then from  to  he practiced law at the law firm of andrews  kurth early political careeredit bakers first wife the former mary stuart mchenry was active in the republican party working on the congressional campaigns of george h w bush originally baker had been a democrat but too busy trying to succeed in a competitive law firm to worry about politics and considered himself apolitical his wifes influence led baker to politics and the republican party he was a regular tennis partner of george h w bush at the houston country club in the late s when bush sr decided to vacate his congressional seat and run for the us senate in  he supported bakers decision to run for the congressional seat he was vacating however baker changed his mind about running for congress when his wife was diagnosed with breast cancer she died in february  bush sr then encouraged baker to become active in politics to help deal with the grief of his wifes death something that bush sr himself had done when his daughter pauline robinson – died of leukemia baker became chairman of bushs senate campaign in harris county texas though bush lost to lloyd bentsen in the election baker continued in politics becoming the finance chairman of the republican party in  the following year he was selected as gulf coast regional chairman for the richard nixon presidential campaign in  and  in the wake of the nixon administrations implosion baker returned to fulltime law practice at andrews  kurth bakers time away from politics was very brief however he served as undersecretary of commerce for president gerald ford and ran fords unsuccessful  election campaign in  with george h w bush as his campaign manager baker ran unsuccessfully for attorney general of texas losing to future texas governor mark white reagan administrationedit the troika from left to right chief of staff james baker counselor to the president ed meese deputy chief of staff michael deaver at the white house december   in  baker was named white house chief of staff by president ronald reagan in spite of the fact that baker managed the presidential campaigns of gerald ford in  and of george bush in  opposing reagan he served in that capacity until  baker is considered to have had a high degree of influence over the first reagan administration particularly in domestic policy in  conservative activists howard phillips founder of the conservative caucus and clymer wright of houston joined in an unsuccessful effort to convince reagan to dismiss baker as chief of staff they claimed that baker a former democrat and a bush political intimate was undermining conservative initiatives in the administration reagan rejected the phillipswright request but in  he named baker as united states secretary of the treasury in a jobswap with then secretary donald t regan a former merrill lynch officer who became chief of staff reagan rebuked phillips and wright for having waged a campaign of sabotage against baker baker managed reagans  reelection campaign in which reagan polled a record  electoral votes total of  possible and received  percent of the popular vote to walter mondales  percent while serving as treasury secretary baker organized the plaza accord of september  and the baker plan to target international debt he had richard darman of massachusetts as his deputy secretary of the treasury darman would continue in the next administration as the director of the office of management and budget in  baker received the us senator john heinz award for greatest public service by an elected or appointed official an award given out annually by jefferson awards during the reagan administration baker also served on the economic policy council where he played an instrumental role in achieving the passage of the administrations tax and budget reform package in  he also played a role in the development of the silver eagle and the gold eagle which both were released in  baker also served on reagans national security council and remained treasury secretary until  during which time he also served as campaign chairman for george h w bushs successful presidential bid bush administrationedit see also george hw bush § foreign policy president george hw bush appointed baker secretary of state in  baker served in this role through  from  to  he served as bushs white house chief of staff the same position that he had held from  to  during the first reagan administration on january   during the geneva peace conference with tariq aziz in geneva baker declared that if there is any user of chemical or biological weapons our objectives wont just be the liberation of kuwait but the elimination of the current iraqi regime baker later acknowledged that the intent of this statement was to threaten a retaliatory nuclear strike on iraq and the iraqis received his message baker helped to construct the nation alliance that fought alongside the united states in the gulf war he was awarded the presidential medal of freedom in  baker arriving in kuwait  baker blocked the creation of palestine by threatening to cut funding to agencies in the united nations as far back as  the palestine liberation organization plo issued a declaration of statehood” and changed the name of its observer delegation to the united nations from the plo to palestine baker warned publicly i will recommend to the president that the united states make no further contributions voluntary or assessed to any international organization which makes any changes in the plos status as an observer organization postcabinet careeredit –edit external video booknotes interview with baker on the politics of diplomacy revolution war and peace  december   cspan in  baker became the honorary chair of the james a baker iii institute of public policy at rice university in houston texas also in  the enron corporation hired baker as a consultant within a month of his departure from the white house and enron said that baker would have an opportunity to invest in any projects he developed in  baker published his memoirs of service as secretary of state in a book entitled the politics of diplomacy revolution war and peace – isbn  in march  baker became the personal envoy of the un secretarygeneral for western sahara in june  he resigned from this position frustrated over the lack of progress in reaching a complete settlement acceptable to both the government of morocco and the proindependence polisario front he left behind the baker ii plan accepted as a suitable basis of negotiations by the polisario and unanimously endorsed by the security council but rejected by morocco in addition to the numerous recognitions received by baker he was presented with the prestigious woodrow wilson award for public service on september   in washington dc in  baker served as chief legal adviser for george w bush during the  election campaign and oversaw the florida recount the  film recount covers the days following the controversial election during the making of the film baker was interviewed baker was portrayed in the film by british actor tom wilkinson on september   baker watched television coverage of the attacks on the world trade center and the pentagon from the ritzcarlton hotel in washington dc where baker and representatives of osama bin ladens family were among those attending the annual conference for the carlyle group baker is senior counselor for the carlyle group and the bin ladens are among its major investorsdubious – discuss state of denial a book by investigative reporter bob woodward says that white house chief of staff andrew card urged president bush to replace secretary of defense donald rumsfeld with baker following the  election however another g h w bush administration veteran robert gates was appointed instead and only after the  elections baker was elected a fellow of the american academy of arts and sciences in  iraqedit in december  president george w bush appointed baker as his special envoy to ask various foreign creditor nations to forgive or restructure  billion in international debts owed by the iraq government which had been incurred during the tenure of saddam hussein on march   congress announced the formation of the iraq study group a highlevel panel of prominent former officials charged by members of congress with taking a fresh look at americas policy on iraq baker was the republican cochairman along with democratic congressman lee h hamilton to advise congress on iraq baker also advised george w bush on iraq the iraq study group examined a number of ideas including one that would create a new powersharing arrangement in iraq that would give more autonomy to regional factions on october   the washington post quoted cochairman baker as saying our commission believes that there are alternatives between the stated alternatives the ones that are out there in the political debate of stay the course and cut and run other advisory positionsedit baker serves on the honorary council of advisers for the usazerbaijan chamber of commerce in  baker was a member of a small group of republican elder statesmen proposing that conservatives embrace carbon taxes with all revenue rebated with lumpsum dividends as a policy to deal with global climate change the group also included martin s feldstein n gregory mankiw henry m paulson jr and george p shultz world justice projectedit james baker serves as an honorary cochair for the world justice project the world justice project works to lead a global multidisciplinary effort to strengthen the rule of law for the development of communities of opportunity and equity climate leadership counciledit baker is a leader of the climate leadership council along with henry paulson and george p shultz personal lifeedit baker met his first wife the former mary stuart mchenry of dayton ohio while on spring break in bermuda with the princeton university rugby team they married in  together they had four sons mary stuart baker mary stuart was her full first name died of breast cancer in february  in  baker and susan garrett winston a widow and a close friend of mary stuart were married she had two sons and a daughter with her late husband she and baker welcomed their daughter mary bonner baker born in  on june   virginia graeme baker the sevenyearold granddaughter of baker daughter of nancy and james baker iv was the victim of lethal suctionpump entrapment in an inground spa to promote greater safety in pools and spas nancy baker gave testimony to the consumer product safety commission and james baker helped form an advocacy group which led to the virginia graeme baker pool and spa safety act  usc  honorsedit grand cordon of the order of the rising sun  notesedit  biographies of the secretaries of state james addison baker iii us department of state office of the historian retrieved november     about the baker institute james a baker iii institute for public policy retrieved september     city of houston procedures for historic district designation archived june   at the wayback machine city of houston adobe acrobat pdf document retrieved july    mother of secretary of state baker dies here at  houston chronicle april   retrieved july    james a baker rd current biography march  retrieved december   like his father jim baker as he prefers to be known attended the hill school a college prep school in pottstown pennsylvania then enrolled at princeton university  newhouse john profiles the tactician the new yorker may   pp– retrieved july    a b public policy papers department of rare books and special collections princeton university library collection creator biography james a baker iii papers  retrieved  may  cs maint multiple names authors list link  james a baker iii work hard study and keep out of politics new york    phil gailey and warren weaver jr briefing the new york times june   june   retrieved january      national results us election atlas  national winners  public service awards  jefferson awardsorg jeffersonawardsorg retrieved    nndb profile  nndb white house chief of staff list  lawrence freedman and efraim karsh the gulf conflict diplomacy and war in the new world order new jersey    plague war interviews james baker frontline pbs    sadams toxic arsenal planning the unthinkable isbn   james baker the man who made washington work pbs   bolton john june   how to block the palestine statehood ploy the wall street journal subscription required help   baker and mosbacher are hired by enron nytimescom retrieved    un envoy asking baker to resolve dispute is good choice houston chronicle march    james baker nndbcom retrieved    book of members – chapter b pdf american academy of arts and sciences retrieved april     king john “bush appoints baker envoy on iraqi debt” “cnncom” december   retrieved august    paley amit r us and iraqi forces clash with sadr militia in south washington post october    baker surfaces as key adviser to bush on iraq insight magazine september    sanger david e gops baker hints iraq plan needs change new york times october    honorary council of advisers archived december   at the wayback machine  us azerbaijan chamber of commerce  httpswwwclcouncilorgwpcontentuploadstheconservativecaseforcarbondividendspdf  httpswwwnytimescomscienceaconservativeclimatesolutionrepublicangroupcallsforcarbontaxhtml  john schwartz february   ‘a conservative climate solution’ republican group calls for carbon tax the new york times retrieved april   the group led by former secretary of state james a baker iii with former secretary of state george p shultz and henry m paulson jr a former secretary of the treasury says that taxing carbon pollution produced by burning fossil fuels is “a conservative climate solution” based on freemarket principles   dumas bob troubled waters pool  spa news october   chow shernmin former secretary of state pushes for hot tub safety standards vacalert june    press releases former secretary of state james baker speaks in support of legislation intended to prevent accidental drowning safe kids worldwide may    virginia graeme baker pool and spa safety act archived may   at the wayback machine consumer product safety commission at vacalert adobe acrobat pdf document further readingedit works byedit  the politics of diplomacy with thomas m defrank new york gp putnams sons isbn   work hard study and keep out of politics adventures and lessons from an unexpected public life with steve fiffer new york gp putnams sons isbn  works aboutedit bryce robert  cronies oil the bushes and the rise of texas americas superstate new york perseus books group isbn  external linksedit wikiquote has quotations related to james baker baker james iiiwoodson research center fondren library rice university houston tx usa james addison baker papers at the seeley g mudd manuscript library princeton university james a baker iii oral history collection at the seeley g mudd manuscript library princeton university profile in the daily princetonian biography on baker botts llp website baker institute for public policy appearances on cspan james baker oral history at houston oral history project november   political 